        Do You Need a Solicitor or Conveyancer When Selling in Queensland?
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1rem;color:rgba(240,236,228,0.6);line-height:1.8;max-width:54ch;">
        Queensland property law requires professional legal representation when selling. Here is what that means in practice, what it costs, and when to engage one.
      </p>
